exercises.name: Push-Up
exercises.description: A classic bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the chest muscles, while also engaging the triceps and shoulders. Push-ups are great for building upper body strength and endurance.
instructions: Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Push back up to the starting position.
Keep your core tight throughout the movement.

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: An intense full-body exercise that improves cardiovascular endurance and strength by engaging multiple muscle groups in one dynamic movement.
instructions: Start in a standing position.
Drop into a squat with your hands on the floor.
Kick your feet back into a plank position.
Perform a push-up, then jump your feet back to the squat position.
Explosively jump into the air, reaching your arms overhead.

exercises.name: Mountain Climbers
exercises.description: A core-strengthening exercise that also boosts heart rate, targeting the abs, legs, and shoulders in a fast-paced movement.
instructions: Start in a high plank position.
Drive your right knee toward your chest.
Quickly switch legs, bringing your left knee toward your chest.
Continue alternating legs as fast as possible.

exercises.name: Jumping Jacks
exercises.description: A full-body exercise that helps improve cardiovascular endurance and coordination by engaging both the upper and lower body.
instructions: Start standing with your feet together and hands at your sides.
Jump your feet out to the sides while raising your arms overhead.
Quickly reverse the movement, returning to the starting position.
Repeat continuously.

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.description: A static core exercise that strengthens the abdominal muscles and improves overall stability.
instructions: Start in a forearm plank position with your body in a straight line.
Hold the position while keeping your core tight.
Avoid letting your hips drop or rise.
Maintain for the desired amount of time.

exercises.name: Squat to Press
exercises.description: A compound exercise that targets both the lower body and shoulders, improving strength and coordination.
instructions: Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Perform a squat, lowering your body as if sitting back into a chair.
As you return to standing, press your hands overhead.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Lunge to Knee Drive
exercises.description: A dynamic exercise that targets the legs and core while improving balance and coordination.
instructions: Start in a standing position.
Step forward with your right leg and lower into a lunge.
Drive your right knee up toward your chest as you stand back up.
Repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: High Knees
exercises.description: A cardio-intensive exercise that engages the legs and core, promoting cardiovascular endurance and strength.
instructions: Start standing with your feet hip-width apart.
Run in place, driving your knees toward your chest as high as possible.
Keep your core engaged and maintain a fast pace.

exercises.name: Inchworm
exercises.description: A full-body exercise that engages the core, shoulders, and legs through a series of bodyweight movements.
instructions: Start standing with your feet hip-width apart.
Bend at your hips and walk your hands forward into a plank position.
Perform a push-up, then walk your hands back to your feet and stand up.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Spider-Man Push-Up
exercises.description: A variation of the push-up that enhances core stability and targets the chest, triceps, and legs in a coordinated movement.
instructions: Start in a high plank position.
As you lower into a push-up, bring your right knee toward your right elbow.
Push back up to the starting position and return your leg.
Repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Squat
exercises.description: A foundational lower-body exercise that strengthens the legs, glutes, and core while promoting balance and stability.
instructions: Start with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body as if sitting back into a chair.
Keep your chest up and knees behind your toes.
Return to standing and repeat.

exercises.name: Glute Bridge
exercises.description: An exercise that isolates the glute muscles while also engaging the hamstrings and core, perfect for building posterior strength.
instructions: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Lift your hips toward the ceiling, squeezing your glutes at the top.
Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: A unilateral exercise that targets the quads, glutes, and core, improving balance and leg strength.
instructions: Start in a standing position.
Step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are at 90-degree angles.
Push back up to the starting position and switch legs.
Repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Step-Ups
exercises.description: A functional lower-body exercise that mimics everyday movements, targeting the legs and glutes.
instructions: Stand in front of a step or bench.
Step up with one foot, then bring the other foot up to meet it.
Step back down one foot at a time and repeat.

exercises.name: Donkey Kicks
exercises.description: An effective exercise for isolating the glutes and improving lower-body strength and stability.
instructions: Start on all fours with your hands under your shoulders and knees under your hips.
Lift one leg, keeping your knee bent at 90 degrees.
Push your heel toward the ceiling, squeezing your glutes.
Lower back down and repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Wall Sit
exercises.description: A static lower-body exercise that strengthens the quads and core while testing endurance.
instructions: Stand with your back against a wall and feet shoulder-width apart.
Slide down the wall until your knees are at 90-degree angles.
Hold the position, keeping your core tight.
Stand back up and repeat.

exercises.name: Calf Raises
exercises.description: A simple yet effective exercise for strengthening the calf muscles and improving balance.
instructions: Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Rise up onto the balls of your feet, lifting your heels off the ground.
Hold for a second, then lower back down.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Side Lunges
exercises.description: A lateral movement that targets the inner and outer thighs, glutes, and core for improved leg strength and balance.
instructions: Start standing with your feet together.
Step out to the side with one leg, bending that knee while keeping the other leg straight.
Push back to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Deadlift
exercises.description: An advanced lower-body exercise that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and core while improving balance.
instructions: Start standing with your feet together.
Lift one leg behind you while keeping your back straight.
Lower your torso toward the floor while balancing on the other leg.
Return to the starting position and switch legs.

exercises.name: Bridge March
exercises.description: A core and glute-focused exercise that builds strength in the posterior chain through alternating leg lifts in a bridge position.
instructions: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Lift your hips into a bridge position.
Lift one knee toward your chest, then lower it back down.
Repeat on the other side while keeping your hips lifted.

exercises.name: Pull-Up
exercises.description: A challenging upper-body exercise that targets the back and biceps, promoting overall upper body strength.
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you.
Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar.
Lower back down to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: An upper-body exercise that primarily targets the triceps while also engaging the chest and shoulders.
instructions: Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands next to your hips.
Slide your hips off the bench and lower your body by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Pike Push-Up
exercises.description: A bodyweight shoulder exercise that also strengthens the triceps and core, ideal for improving upper-body stability.
instructions: Start in a downward dog position with your hips raised and hands on the floor.
Lower your head toward the floor by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Inverted Row
exercises.description: A bodyweight pulling exercise that targets the back and biceps, improving upper body pulling strength.
instructions: Lie on your back under a bar or table with your feet on the floor.
Grip the bar with your hands shoulder-width apart.
Pull your chest up toward the bar, keeping your body straight.
Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Decline Push-Up
exercises.description: A variation of the traditional push-up that targets the upper chest and shoulders, building upper-body strength.
instructions: Start in a high plank position with your feet elevated on a bench or step.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Superman
exercises.description: A bodyweight exercise that targets the lower back, glutes, and hamstrings, improving posterior chain strength.
instructions: Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended in front of you.
Lift your arms, chest, and legs off the floor simultaneously.
Hold the position for a few seconds, then lower back down.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Diamond Push-Up
exercises.description: A push-up variation that places more emphasis on the triceps and chest, enhancing upper body strength.
instructions: Start in a high plank position with your hands close together, forming a diamond shape.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches your hands.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Plank to Push-Up
exercises.description: A dynamic core and upper-body exercise that improves core stability and upper body strength through plank and push-up transitions.
instructions: Start in a forearm plank position.
Push up onto your hands one at a time, transitioning into a high plank.
Lower back down to your forearms and repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Dive Bomber Push-Up
exercises.description: An advanced push-up variation that engages the chest, shoulders, triceps, and core in a flowing movement pattern.
instructions: Start in a downward dog position with your hips raised.
Lower your chest toward the floor in a swooping motion, then push up into a cobra pose.
Reverse the movement back to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Handstand Push-Up
exercises.description: An advanced bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the shoulders, requiring significant core and upper body strength.
instructions: Start in a handstand position against a wall.
Lower your head toward the floor by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat the movement.
